# User-private benchmark fixtures.
# The hand-labelled task JSONs in benchmarks/cross_repo/ encode
# repo-specific directory structure and feature vocabulary in their
# `expected` paths and `question` strings, which together identify
# the underlying codebases to anyone familiar with them. They are
# kept locally for reproduction but never tracked in version control.
# The schema (cross_repo/README.md) and the harness scripts
# (benchmarks/parity_vs_ripgrep.py, etc.) remain checked in so an
# independent reader can build their own fixtures and reproduce the
# protocol.
benchmarks/cross_repo/*.json
